### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

common

### Description

In our current application we have a custom image component which uses `HttpClient` to fetch images, to allow showing a "broken image" icon for when the image fails to load. This should be supported in `NgOptimizedImage` to provide a cleaner UI when images fail to load properly.

### Proposed solution

Allow us to pass an alternative url as an `@Input` to the `NgOptimizedImage`, and set metadata on the `img` element so developers can know if the placeholder image is rendered or not, and style it accordingly if needed. 

### Alternatives considered

With the new control-flow syntax, perhaps it could be possible to have something like `@image/@error` blocks, allowing you to pass custom elements altogether if the image fails to load. This way would allow more control than the previously suggested idea. Something like:

```
@image {
  <img ngSrc="cat.jpg" />
}
@error {
  <my-fallback-component>
    <app-icon icon="broken-image" />
    The image could not be loaded :(
  </my-fallback-component>
}
```

As seen in https://github.com/angular/angular/pull/53465 and explained to me by @alxhub memory alloc is expensive. So i've created this new pullrequest with a new version that i'm just going to leave it as a drafted pull request.

The idea is to avoid allocating extra memory by packing the numeric values of the edges 'Version & indexOfThis' into one numeric value using bitwise operators.

I've tested this against this benchsuite https://github.com/leonelvsc/js-reactivity-benchmark/tree/patch2 `patch2` branch, i've compiled the angular sources for testing with this refactor.

